{"title_page": "Fred Daspit", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Fred Daspit\n| birth_name = \n| image  = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = c. 1931\n| birth_place = [[St. Martinville, Louisiana]], U.S.\n| death_date = July 8, 2014\n| death_place = [[Lafayette, Louisiana]], U.S.\n| resting place = \n| education = [[University of Louisiana at Lafayette]]<br/>[[Louisiana State University]]\n| occupation = \n| spouse = \n| children = \n| other_names = \n| parents = \n| relatives = \n}}\n'''Fred Daspit''' (c. 1931 - July 8, 2014) was an American artist and academic. He taught art and architecture at the [[University of Louisiana at Lafayette]], and he authored three books about the antebellum architecture of Louisiana.<ref name=\"dailyadvertiserobit\">{{cite news |last1=Cross |first1=Dominick |title=Fred Daspit, beloved professor, artist, dies at 83 |url=https://theadvertiser.com/story/news/local/2014/07/09/fred-daspit-beloved-professor-artist-dies/12437319/ |accessdate=January 25, 2020 |work=Daily Advertiser |date=July 10, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"independentobit\">{{cite news |last1=Turk |first1=Leslie |title=Artist, lifelong educator Fred Daspit dies at 83 |url=http://theind.com/article-17825-artist-lifelong-educator-fred-daspit-dies-at-83.html |accessdate=January 25, 2020 |work=The Independent |date=July 9, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n*{{cite book |last1=Daspit |first1=Fred |title=Louisiana Architecture, 1714-1820 |date=2004 |publisher=University of Louisiana at Lafayette |location=Lafayette, Louisiana |isbn=9781887366601|oclc=59225810}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Daspit |first1=Fred |title=Louisiana Architecture, 1820-1840 |date=2005 |publisher=University of Louisiana at Lafayette |location=Lafayette, Louisiana |isbn=9781887366588|oclc=728068654}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Daspit |first1=Fred |title=Louisiana Architecture, 1840-1860 |date=2006 |publisher=University of Louisiana at Lafayette |location=Lafayette, Louisiana |isbn=978