l\n | xAxisTitle= Date\n | yAxisTitle=No. of new Recovered \n}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n | width = 800\n | type = rect\n | yGrid =\n | xGrid =\n | xAxisAngle = -70\n | colors=Tomato\n | x = 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar,21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr, 2 Apr, 3 Apr, 4 Apr, 5 Apr, 6 Apr\n | y = 1, 3, 4, 5, 7, 10, 13, 17, 23, 34, 43, 61, 75, 156, 200, 235, 337, 428, 528, 623, 733, 903, 1117, 1269, 1562, 1842, 2057, 2285, 2570, 2781, 3051, 3288, 3606, 3839, 4050\n | legend=Legend\n | showValues=offset:2\n | y1Title = Active cases\n | xAxisTitle= Date\n | yAxisTitle= No. of active cases\n}}\n\n==Government response==\n*'''13 March 2020''': President [[Sebasti\u00e1n Pi\u00f1era]] announced a ban on public events with more than 500 people, as the government tries to control the spread of coronavirus even as massive social demonstrations are planned in March and April months.<ref name=\"Response_1\">{{cite news |title=Chile bans large public events over coronavirus fears, ahead of planned protests|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-chile/chile-bans-large-public-events-over-coronavirus-fears-ahead-of-planned-protests-idUSKBN21102N |accessdate=13 March 2020 |work=reuters|issue=Mar2020 |publisher=reuters.com|date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n*'''14 March 2020''': Nearly 1,300 passengers on two cruises in Chile have been quarantined after an 83-year-old British national tested positive for coronavirus.<ref name=\"Response_2\">{{cite news |title=Chile quarantines 1,300 cruise passengers after Brit, 83, catches coronavirus|url=https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/15/chile-quarantines-1300-cruise-passengers-brit-83-catches-coronavirus-12399822/ |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=metro.co.uk|issue=Mar2020 |publisher=metro.co.uk}}</ref> [[Caleta Tortel]], a small coastal village that had been visited by the aforementioned tourist was subsequently placed under a 14-day quarantine.<ref>{{cite news |title=Caleta Tortel inicia cuarentena y suspenden servicios de transporte en la comuna |url=https://radio.uchile.cl/2020/03/15/caleta-tortel-inicia-cuarentena-y-suspenden-servicios-de-transporte-en-la-comuna/ |accessdate=19 March 2020 |work=Radio UChile|issue=Mar2020 |publisher=radio.uchile.cl|date=15 March 2020 |language=es-ES}}</ref>\n*'''15 March 2020''': President Pi\u00f1era announced below points regarding student in a press conference\n# 14-day isolation for any member of an educational community who has a direct relative with confirmed contagion.\n# Suspension of classes for 14 days of the complete course when a student has confirmed contagion.\n# Suspension of classes for 14 days from the complete educational establishment in the case of two or more cases of students with confirmed contagion. These measures may be modified or extended to specific territories, such as communes and regions, as necessary.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n*'''16 March 2020''': President Pi\u00f1era announced the closure of the borders for 14 days. He said \u201cWe have decided to close all land, sea and area borders of our country for the transit of foreign people. This will not affect the entry and exit of cargo or carriers, to continue guaranteeing a normal supply of our country. This measure will take effect from 18 March 2020. Chilean nationals and permanent residents in Chile, who come from high-risk places, may enter our country undergoing Sanitary Customs and a mandatory 14-day quarantine.<ref name=\"Cases_155\"/>\n*'''18 March 2020''': President Pi\u00f1era issued a 90-day state of catastrophe ''(a [[state of exception]] subtype regulated in the [[Constitution of Chile]])'' in order to control the spread of the virus, effective at midnight.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus en Chile: Pi\u00f1era decreta estado de cat\u00e1strofe por 90 d\u00edas |url=https://oasisfm.cl/oasis-hoy/coronavirus-en-chile-pinera-decreta-estado-de-catastrofe-por-90-dias |accessdate=18 March 2020 |work=Oasis FM|issue=Mar2020 |publisher=oasisfm.cl|language=es-ES}}</ref>\n*'''20 March 2020''': The mayors of Las Condes, La Reina and Vitacura declared a preventive quarantine for these sectors of the capital, where a large number of confirmed cases of coronavirus were recorded.<ref>{{cite news |title=Alcaldes de Vitacura, La Reina y Las Condes anuncian cuarentena preventiva en sus comunas |url=https://www.cnnchile.com/coronavirus/cuarentena-preventiva-la-reina-vitacura-las-condes_20200320/ |accessdate=20 March 2020 |work=cnnchile|issue=Mar2020 |publisher=cnnchile|language=en}}</ref>\n*'''22 March 2020''': Chile announced a nationwide, night-time curfew between 22:00 Hrs to 5:00 Hrs to keep people off the streets and away from one another as the number of cases of coronavirus continued to creep upwards in the South American nation.<ref name=\"Cases_632\">{{cite news |title=Chile announces nationwide nightly curfew, coronavirus cases hit 632 |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/chile-announces-nationwide-nightly-curfew-coronavirus-cases-hit-632 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=nationalpost|issue=Mar2020 |publisher=nationalpost|language=En}}</ref>\n*'''22 March 2020''': The curfew was extended from 10pm-5am to 2pm-5am in Easter Island.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ampl\u00edan toque de queda en Isla de Pascua por primer caso de COVID-19: desde las 14 horas hasta las 5 de la ma\u00f1ana |url=http://lanacion.cl/2020/03/24/amplian-toque-de-queda-en-isla-de-pascua-por-primer-caso-de-covid-19-desde-las-14-horas-hasta-las-5-de-la-manana/|accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=La Naci\u00f3n|issue=Mar2020 |publisher=lanacion.cl|language=Es}}</ref>\n*'''26 March 2020''': At 10pm, a complete lockdown is established in 7 communes of [[Santiago, Chile|Greater Santiago]] ([[Santiago (commune)|Santiago]], [[Independencia, Chile|Independencia]], [[Providencia, Chile|Providencia]], [[\u00d1u\u00f1oa]], [[Las Condes]], [[Vitacura]], and [[Lo Barnechea]]), covering 1.3 million inhabitants.\n*'''28 March 2020''': At 10pm, a complete lockdown is established in [[Temuco]] and [[Padre Las Casas, Chile|Padre las Casas]].\n*'''1 April 2020''': At 10pm, a complete lockdown is established in [[Punta Arenas, Chile]].\n\n== Reactions ==\nOn 2 March 2020, The CRU World Copper Conference in [[Santiago]] the largest annual gathering of copper miners in the world was canceled which was scheduled between 23 and 27 March 2020, due to concerns over travel risks associated with the coronavirus pandemic.<ref name=\"Reaction1\">{{Cite news |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/chile-copper/update-1-world-copper-conference-in-chile-canceled-over-coronavirus-concerns-cesco-idUSL1N2AV0P7 |title=UPDATE 1-World Copper Conference in Chile canceled over coronavirus concerns - Cesco |accessdate=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nMassive events such as [[Lollapalooza Chile]] (scheduled between 27 and 29 March 2020) and the [[FIDAE|XXI International Air and Space Fair]] (scheduled to take place between 31 March and 5 April), have been preventively suspended.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latercera.com/la-tercera-pm/noticia/lollapalooza-para-noviembre-metallica-y-kiss-en-suspenso-teleton-casi-sin-pubico-el-dificil-semestre-que-espera-a-los-eventos-en-chile/4VNVHUMCZ5CUHADRJ5QBNLG5DA/|title=Lollapalooza para noviembre, Metallica y Kiss en suspenso, Telet\u00f3n casi sin p\u00fablico: el Coronavirus contagia a los eventos en Chile|accessdate=13 March 2020|date=12 March 2020|website=La Tercera|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latercera.com/nacional/noticia/presidente-pinera-anuncia-que-se-suspendera-la-fidae-por-el-coronavirus/I6A5JH4KFBCILNHJOSU645O2EI/|title=Presidente Pi\u00f1era anuncia que se suspender\u00e1 la Fidae por el coronavirus|accessdate=13 March 2020|date=13 March 2020|website=La Tercera|language=es}}</ref> However, the Chilean government has assured that the [[2020 Chilean national plebiscite|26 April National Plebiscite]] will be held under sanitary safeguard measures.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.latercera.com/nacional/noticia/manalich-asegura-que-gobierno-no-tiene-previsto-cancelar-plebiscito-por-coronavirus-no-anticipo-que-haya-una-discusion-respecto-a-la-pertinencia-de-hacerlo/RLNT27PYF5CEFALFZLUSLIDRE4/|title=Ma\u00f1alich asegura que gobierno no tiene previsto cancelar plebiscito por coronavirus: \"No anticipo que haya una discusi\u00f3n respecto a la pertinencia de hacerlo\"|accessdate=13 March 2020|date=13 March 2020|website=La Tercera|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 March 2020, Chilean lawmakers had reached agreement to postpone the referendum on a new constitution until late October as safety concerns around the coronavirus pandemic take precedence over politics. The referendum, originally slated for 26 April 2020 will be rescheduled for 25 October 2020, However the deal still requires formal approval by a two-thirds vote of congress.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-chile/chile-to-postpone-referendum-on-new-constitution-as-coronavirus-concerns-grow-idUSKBN2163TL|title=Chile to postpone referendum on new constitution as coronavirus concerns grow\n|accessdate=19 March 2020|date=19 March 2020|website=reuters|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.minsal.cl/nuevo-coronavirus-2019-ncov/casos-confirmados-en-chile-covid-19/ Official Chile's government confirmed cases in Chile COVID-19 Report]\n* [https://datastudio.google.com/u/0/reporting/f97733c1-17e1-4bd6-8841-9dd2d45ac9b4/page/W3OJB/ COVID-19 Chile Dashboard]\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Chile|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Chile]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in South America|Chile]]\n[[Category:2020 in Chile|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Chile]]\n